You're becoming a real pro mate :P <p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1><span class=m> </span></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub103.ezboard.com/ubbarden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bbarden</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.bbarden.com/userfiles/bb-icon.jpg" BORDER=0> </span><br> <span class=usertitle>Animated Block Bloke<br /><img src='http://www.bbarden.com/img/levels/userlevel-ezop.gif' /></span><br>  ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.bbarden.com/userfiles/squares.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top width=80% class=m><span class=title>   Re: :D</span><br><span class=m><font color=#FF0000>Posted: 6/17/02 3:59:18 pm</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>    <hr size=1> Thanks for the comments, kirbz.  Before I continue with my reply, please note that this is not directly aimed at you, I'm just explaining my reasons for the redesign.<br>
<br>
If you read a bit further up the thread, you'll see that I've already addressed this - it's deliberate.  It is just how I designed it.<br>
<br>
If you browse around the rest of the web site, you will see that the home page is not the only one that looks the way it does.<br>
<br>
I didn't want a line of text to stretch across the entire screen - it is very difficult to read web pages that do that.  However, I didn't want to clutter things up by keeping the sidebar we had before.  So I went for an empty margin.<br>
<br>
The tables are right justified and not centred because I wanted to be different.  In fact that's one of the defining factors of the bbarden network - &quot;be who you want to be&quot; meaning that we're not a typical web site.<br>
<br>
I actually think that this design looks more &quot;controlled&quot; than a centrally aligned look.  What happens when you resize your browser?  The whole table resizes.  Unless you use fixed width (as I did before), in which case you can NEVER resize the main table.  This way, only the right hand side of the screen resizes.  I've gone for a &quot;half and half&quot; approach.<br>
<br>
I'm working on making the stylesheets control the fonts a lot better, so you can use the &quot;text size&quot; browser setting if you can't read the fonts very easily.<br>
<br>
I'm trying to make the site easier to view for more people... I realise it is going to take a little bit of time to adjust.  But it's going to be easier in the long run (hopefully!!).<br>
<br>
Anyway, that's why I've done this new look... that, and we needed a change <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.bbarden.com/img/em/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
